<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="120" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="120" type="mainText">
Diagnosis. The genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Psilodercidae" genus="Althepus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Althepus</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName pageId="1" pageNumber="120" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Psilodercinae">Psilodercinae</taxonomicName>
and can be distinguished from other genera of this subfamily by the combination of following characters: retromargin of chelicerae with 2 teeth or denticles; ratio dorsal prosoma length / clypeus length&gt; 3; tarsus of male palp with lateral protrusion bearing a lanceolate apophysis (= modified seta), short bulb with embolus and conductor widely separated (Deeleman-Reinhold 1995).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
